            <fr:title text="n-truncated types are closed under retracts › "><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003S.xml" title="n-truncated types are closed under retracts" addr="//erct/erct-003S" type="local"><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="//erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link> types are closed under <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0025.xml" title="Retract" addr="//erct/erct-0025" type="local">retracts</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By induction on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>; the base cases for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-2]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-1]]></fr:tex> are given by <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002V.xml" title="The identity map is n-truncated for all n" addr="//erct/erct-002V" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002V" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0026.xml" title="Propositions are closed under retracts" addr="//erct/erct-0026" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-0026" /></fr:link> respectively. In the inductive step, we assume that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> exhibits <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> as a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0025.xml" title="Retract" addr="//erct/erct-0025" type="local">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and that for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=_Ay]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="//erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link> to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u,v:B]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=_Bv]]></fr:tex> is likewise <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="//erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link>. The result follows from our assumption and the fact that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=_Bv]]></fr:tex> is (by <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003U.xml" title="Lifting retracts to identifications" addr="//erct/erct-003U" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-003U" /></fr:link>) a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0025.xml" title="Retract" addr="//erct/erct-0025" type="local">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[su=_Asv]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
